@Node "Ques" "Questions"
 
 @{b}Questions@{ub}

 Q: How do I make a really good explosion with more faces than the actual
    object has without taking too long to render?

 A: Simple, just make three different spheres (normal mesh amount should do).
    One with a red colour (no texture for speed), one yellow and one white,
    and if you have the time, make a black one for debris.
    Now put the spheres INSIDE the object (make them as big as possible  
    without showing them) and add the explosion or shredder effect (whatever
    the main object is using) to add the extra "bits" of the object.



  Q: Is there a way to make an object spin without having to morph it or
     make several key-frames for it?

  A: Yes, add the rotate effect, its much faster than key-framing all the
     time.



  Q: How do I make a "lazer" effect?
 
  A: Most people think of using lights for this, you'll actually find that
     using an object is far better as it can be shaped much easier than light
     (which really can't be shaped at all).
     Make a small cylinder, and make it as long as your want, or whatever, now
     make another one on the outside...
     Make both a bright colour (no texture needed) and make them both 
     tranparent, but the outer layer should only JUST be visible 
     (glowing effect), now join them, and their very easy to use.



  Q: How do I make it look like a Human's eye's view (wide range)?

  A: Set the camera perspective to near maximum, so the image almost BENDS
     around the camera, now make it slightly less (make the perspective window
     full screen to get a better idea what the sizing will be like on a full
     screen render.
     This ads the extra perspective the human eye has.



  Q: What is a realistic motion blur?
  
  A: Set the shutter speed to 24, and make the blur length (frames) 4.




  Unanswered:

